# E2E Testing Rules - Playwright

- Initialize configuration only with Chromium/Desktop Chrome browser
- Use browser contexts for isolating test environments
- Implement the Page Object Model for maintainable tests
- Use `data-testid` attributes when introducing resilient test-oriented selectors
- Leverage parallel execution for faster test runs
- Follow 'Arrange', 'Act', 'Assert' approach to test structure for simplicity and readability.
- Try to write parametrized tests for common actions using Theory.
- Avoid unnecessary comments in code.
- Try to use Shouldly assertions for better readability.
- Use Faker/Bogus for generating test data.